<br>
The original poster said he was lvl 63, so I assumed by that level he has Draught of Thunder, and Probablly epic.  Even if he doesn't have epic, he could get a copy of Force Shield and use that instead.<br>
<br>
Yes the Paladin guards are extremely MR, but draught of Thunder lands well and is easy to channel.  The interrupt component is handy in preventing the guard from healing itself.<br>
<br>
Once you get the hang of it, it really isn't that hard at all.  Don't bother with Fetter, don't bother with snare.  Open with your largest nuke and hope it isn't resisted, and use Draught of Thunder until it dies.  Pull to an out of the way place so that if/when the mob gets in &quot;run away&quot; mode it doesn't walk into adds and force you to lose the kill and zone out.<br>
<br>
I was able to make much more money off of these than off of Hill/Ice giants or groups in Seb.  I was able to kill them faster, and find many more of them available for killing.  Keep trying and learn all of the spawn locations, there are another 5 or so in Felwithe South that are easy to single out if you kill all of the Guards in Felwithe North before respawns. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phlixarcanist>Phlix Arcanist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/24/03 10:21:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26211.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best way to make plat?</span><hr size=1> Step 1) Borrow from rich friends<br>
